Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportMultibit(25.10)                                    reportMultibit(25.10)

Name
       reportMultibit  -  Reports  all the multi-bit flip-flops that have been
       identified during loading the design

Syntax
       reportMultibit

       [-help]

       [-bit <bit_width>]

        [-outFile <file_name>]

       [-cell <cell_name> | -library |  -reasonNotMerged  <unmerged_reason>  |
       -notMergedSummary | -equiv]

       [-cell <cell_name> | -type {comb | latch | flop | seq | iso | ls}]

       [-hinst <hinst_name> | -library | -cell <<cell name>> | -equiv]

       Reports  all  the multi-bit flip-flops that have been identified during
       loading the design. Use  this  command  after  all  the  libraries  are
       loaded.  When  this  command is specified with no parameters, a default
       summary report is printed.  By default, the sequential  cells  will  be
       reported. Both, the multi-bit percentages of flops that are merged, and
       a summary of flops that are not merged is printed.

       There are three basic types of multibit:  sequential, combo, and isola-
       tion/level shifter. This command supports specifying the type of multi-
       bit to report. The -type parameter is a global filter for all other op-
       tions.

       The  default  option  is seq. If -type option is not specified then re-
       porting will take place for sequential cells.

       A set of options separated by a "|" in one "[ ]" listed below cannot be
       used together and the software will report an error in that  case.  Al-
       though  options  from different "[ ]" can be coupled together. The sets
       of mutually exclusive options are provided below.

              * [-cell <cell name> | -library |  -reason_not_merged  <unmerged
                reason> | -not_merged_summary | -equiv ]

              * [-cell <cell name> | -type <type>]

              * [-hinst <hinst> | -library | -cell <cell name> | -equiv ]

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each reportMultibit parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man reportMultibit.

       -bit <bit_width>
              Reports  the  multibit iso/ls cells for the specified bit width.
              The value bit_width can be an integer that represents  the  bit-
              width of the queried isolation/level shifter (iso/ls) cell.

              This  parameter  is  required to be specified when reporting the
              multibit iso/ls cells.

              Example:

              To report 2-bit MB isolation (iso) cells in the design, use  the
              following command:

              reportMultibit -type iso -bit 2

       -cell <cell_name>
              Reports the cell details and equivalence information of a single
              library cell.

       -equiv Reports equivalence summary of the library cells of the selected
              type.

       -hinst <hinst_name>
              Specifies  the  hinst  on which the reporting is to be done. The
              default is the design.

       -library
              Reports the flip-flop/latch equivalence.

              This parameter honors the -type parameter setting.

       -notMergedSummary
              When specified, reports the summary of unmerged instances.

       -outFile <file_name>
              Specifies the name of the output file.

       -reasonNotMerged {All Area BankLabelPartition BankLabelRegister Bus
       CellEquivalent Constraint DRV Distance Legalization Location Partition
       Power ScanConnection Timing Unknown UnmatchedPins User}
              Reports the instances that could not be merged for the specified
              reason. The instance names along with their base cell names  are
              reported.  Specify any of the reasons in the argument or specify
              all to report all instances, their base cell names, and the rea-
              son why they could not be merged.

              All: All the reasons of not merging

              Area: Merging the instances causes area degradation

              BankLabelPartition: Instances belong  to  different  bank  label
              partition

              BankLabelRegister: No equivalent cells available in the library

              Bus: Non-bus flops

              CellEquivalent: No usable equivalent multi-bit flip-flop cell

              Constraint: Constraints by sdc, rule, or user settings

              Distance:  Instances not merged due to distance greater than the
              threshold

              Legalization: MultiBit instance could not be legalized

              DRV: Merging the instances degrades the drv

              Location: Too far away from other flops in the same group

              Partition: Odd number of flops in one partition

              Power: All available multi-bit cells causing power degradation

              ScanConnection: No scan connection to other flops  in  the  same
              group

              Timing:  Exceed critical path threshold or MBFF merging that de-
              grades timing

              Unknown: The instance cannot be identified

              UnmatchedPins: Number of pins are different on the instances

              User: User set to be excluded in flop merge

              The report format is as follows:

              Reason of not merging:  <>

              Unmerged Sequential instances (<>):

              -----------------------------------

              Instance_name cell_name

              Example:

              reportMultibit -type seq -reasonNotMerged <>

              Reason of not merging:  <>

              Unmerged Sequential instances (<>):

              -----------------------------------

              Instance_name cell_name

              udec1/g24106  ND2D3ULVT

              udec1/g24274  ND2D3ULVT

              udec1/g24323  ND2D4ULVT

              udec1/g24335  ND2D2ULVT

       -type {comb | latch | flop | seq | iso | ls}
              Reports for the specified type of cells. By  default,  only  se-
              quentials  are reported. You can specify anyone of the following
              reports:

              comb: reports all multibit cells  implementing  a  combinational
              function. For example, a cell implementing 3 ANDs - so, 6 inputs
              and 3 outputs

              latch:  reports multi-bit latches in the design.

              flop: reports multi-bit flops.

              seq: reports all sequential cells.

              isolation/level shifter (iso/ls): reports multi-bit cells imple-
              menting  a  low  power  function.  For  example, as 8-bit level-
              shifter cell.

              Default: seq

Examples
       Use the following command to print a default  summary  report.  By  de-
       fault, the sequential cells will be reported..

       reportMultibit

